  "prompt": "Which is the best book of maths for preparation of iit - jee?",
  "response": "For the preparation of **IIT-JEE**, the following books are highly recommended by experts, toppers, and coaching institutes. These books are known for their comprehensive coverage of concepts, practice problems, and advanced-level questions:\n\n---\n\n### **Mathematics Books for IIT-JEE Preparation:**\n\n1. **Objective Mathematics by R.D. Sharma**  \n   - Best for building a strong foundation in mathematics.  \n   - Covers both basic and advanced concepts.  \n   - Ideal for Class 11 and Class 12 students.\n\n2. **Higher Algebra by Hall & Knight**  \n   - Focuses on algebra concepts, including inequalities, sequences, series, and equations.  \n   - A must-have for mastering algebra problems.\n\n3. **Problems in Calculus of One Variable by I.A. Maron**  \n   - Excellent for calculus practice.  \n   - Covers limits, continuity, differentiation, integration, and differential equations.\n\n4. **Coordinate Geometry by S.L. Loney**  \n   - A classic book for coordinate geometry.  \n   - Detailed explanations and practice problems.\n\n5. **Trigonometry by S.L. Loney**  \n   - Best for mastering trigonometry concepts.  \n   - Includes both basic and advanced-level problems.\n\n6. Play with Graphs by Amit M. Agarwal**  \n   - Focuses on graphical representation and analysis.  \n   - Helps in understanding concepts visually.\n\n7. **Mathematics for JEE Main & Advanced by Arihant Publications**  \n   - Comprehensive coverage of JEE syllabus.  \n   - Includes theory, solved examples, and practice problems.\n\n8. **Pearson JEE Advanced Mathematics Series**  \n   - Written by renowned authors like G. Tewani.  \n   - Focuses on JEE Advanced-level problems.\n\n9. **Integral Calculus by Arihant**  \n   - Thorough coverage of integration.  \n   - Includes advanced-level problems.\n\n10. **Differential Calculus by Arihant**  \n    - Excellent for differentiation and its applications.  \n    - Practice problems of varying difficulty levels.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n- **NCERT Textbooks:** Start with NCERT for Class 11 and 12 to build a strong foundation.  \n- **Previous Year Papers:** Solve past IIT-JEE papers to understand the exam pattern and difficulty level.  \n- **Mock Tests:** Practice mock tests to improve speed and accuracy.  \n- **Coaching Material:** If you are enrolled in a coaching institute, their study material is also highly beneficial.\n\n---\n\n### **Conclusion:**\nThe \"best\" book depends on your current understanding and preparation level. Start with basic books like **R.D. Sharma** and **NCERT**, then move to advanced books like **Hall & Knight**, **I.A. Maron**, or **Arihant series** for thorough preparation. Consistent practice and problem-solving are key to cracking IIT-JEE Mathematics.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
